window.CATALOG={"source":[["src.csv","CSV","Read delimited text files","a"],["src.tsv","TSV","Read tab-separated files","a"],["src.json","JSON","Read JSON files","a"],["src.jsonl","JSONL / NDJSON","Read newline-delimited JSON","a"],["src.xml","XML","Read XML files via the pure-Rust `quick-xml` parser. rowPath is a slash-separated element walk (e.g. `library/books/book`); every matching element becomes one row. Attributes prefix with `@`, text content goes to `_text`, nested children nest; repeated same-name siblings collapse to arrays.","a"],["src.excel","Excel (XLSX)","Read .xlsx via the DuckDB excel extension","a"],["src.avro","Avro","Apache Avro container files (.avro / .ocf) via the pure-Rust `apache-avro` crate. The file carries its own schema; engine doesn't need any schema config. Pairs with Kafka topics that publish Avro-encoded payloads.","a"],["src.qvd","Qlik QVD","Qlik QVD files (.qvd) via a clean-room pure-Rust reader (no Qlik runtime). The QVD header carries its own schema; the symbol table + bit-stuffed index are decoded directly. Move QlikView / Qlik Sense extracts into DuckDB, Parquet or any sink.","a"],["src.parquet","Parquet","Read columnar Parquet files","a"],["src.vortex","Vortex","Read Vortex columnar files (.vortex) via the bundled duckle-lance sidecar. Vortex is a next-gen columnar format with fast random access; the sidecar bridges it into the engine through Parquet.","a"],["src.orc","ORC","","p"],["src.fixedwidth","Fixed-width","Read positional / fixed-width text files (mainframe / banking exports). Form provides a columns array - {name, start (1-based), width}; engine builds SUBSTR projections. Trailing whitespace stripped by default.","a"],["src.yaml","YAML","Read a YAML file as a table. Top-level YAML arrays become one row per element; non-array docs become a single row. Suits config-data ETL (Helm values, GitHub Actions matrices) not bulk logs.","a"],["src.toml","TOML","Read a TOML file as a table. Top-level TOML doc becomes one row (TOML disallows a top-level array). Suits Cargo / pyproject / Hugo config audits.","a"],["src.spatial","Geospatial (GeoJSON / Shapefile / GeoPackage)","Read geospatial files via the DuckDB spatial extension (ST_Read)","a"],["src.iceberg","Apache Iceberg","Read Iceberg tables via DuckDB iceberg_scan","a"],["src.delta","Delta Lake","Read Delta Lake tables via DuckDB delta_scan","a"],["src.ducklake","DuckLake","Read tables from a DuckLake catalog (DuckDB native lakehouse)","a"],["src.ducklake.changes","DuckLake CDC","Change-data-feed source: reads table_changes() since the last consumed snapshot (saved in workspace state), emitting row-level insert / delete / update_preimage / update_postimage with a change_type column. True incremental CDC for DuckLake-managed tables.","a"],["src.ducklake.diff","DuckLake Data Diff","Data diff between two snapshots of a DuckLake table: emits the row-level change feed (insert / delete / update_preimage / update_postimage with a change_type column) between a chosen From and To snapshot. Pick snapshots with Browse; wire into a validator to assert expected changes in CI.","a"],["src.postgres","PostgreSQL","Read from PostgreSQL via the DuckDB postgres extension","a"],["src.mysql","MySQL","Read from MySQL via the DuckDB mysql extension","a"],["src.mariadb","MariaDB","Read from MariaDB via the DuckDB mysql extension","a"],["src.sqlserver","SQL Server","Read SQL Server via the native TDS protocol (tiberius, pure Rust). SQL auth (user/password); trust_cert option for self-signed dev servers.","a"],["src.oracle","Oracle","Read Oracle via the official `oracle` Rust crate (ODPI-C). Built into the shipped binary - users need Oracle Instant Client (libclntsh.{so,dll,dylib}) on the library path at RUNTIME; the executor surfaces a clear OCI loader error if it's missing. SQL auth via user / password; EZ Connect string for host:port/service_name.","a"],["src.db2","IBM DB2","","p"],["src.sqlite","SQLite","Read SQLite tables","a"],["src.duckdb","DuckDB","Read a table from a DuckDB file","a"],["src.clickhouse","ClickHouse","Read ClickHouse via the HTTP interface (POST SELECT ... FORMAT JSON). User/password auth via X-ClickHouse-User / X-ClickHouse-Key headers.","a"],["src.cockroach","CockroachDB","Read from CockroachDB via the DuckDB postgres extension","a"],["src.adbc","ADBC (Arrow)","Read any database that ships an ADBC (Arrow Database Connectivity) driver. Point at a prebuilt driver shared library (.dll / .so / .dylib) plus a connection URI and SQL; rows stream back as Arrow for fast loads. Friendly wrappers can map their own fields onto driver / options.","a"],["src.teradata","Teradata","Read from Teradata through its free ODBC driver (no DuckDB Teradata extension exists). Install the Teradata ODBC driver, then connect with friendly host / user / password / database fields, a DSN, or a full ODBC connection string. Whole-table read or custom SQL; types preserved.","a"],["src.jdbc","Generic JDBC","","p"],["src.snowflake","Snowflake","Read Snowflake via the SQL API (/api/v2/statements). Supports PAT and JWT RS256 auth; engine materializes inline result sets as a DuckDB table for downstream stages.","a"],["src.bigquery","BigQuery","Read tables from BigQuery via the duckdb-bigquery community extension - uses standard GCP credential discovery","a"],["src.redshift","Redshift","Read Redshift via the postgres ATTACH path (Redshift speaks Postgres wire on port 5439)","a"],["src.databricks","Databricks SQL","Read Databricks via the SQL Statement Execution API with PAT Bearer auth. Engine materializes inline result sets as a DuckDB table for downstream stages.","a"],["src.synapse","Azure Synapse","Azure Synapse rides the SQL Server TDS wire - same connection form as src.sqlserver.","a"],["src.motherduck","MotherDuck","Read from MotherDuck via ATTACH md:","a"],["src.quack","DuckDB Quack","Read tables from a remote DuckDB instance over the Quack protocol (HTTP on port 9494). Server runs quack_serve(...); client ATTACHes the quack: URL with a token-based SECRET.","a"],["src.gizmosql","GizmoSQL","Query a GizmoSQL (Arrow Flight SQL) server via a clean-room pure-Rust Flight SQL client - no ADBC driver or JDBC needed. Basic-auth handshake then streams Arrow back for fast loads; TLS optional.","a"],["src.s3","Amazon S3","Read via DuckDB httpfs","a"],["src.gcs","Google Cloud Storage","Read via DuckDB httpfs","a"],["src.azureblob","Azure Blob Storage","Read via the azure extension","a"],["src.minio","MinIO","Read via S3-compatible endpoint","a"],["src.r2","Cloudflare R2","Read via S3-compatible endpoint","a"],["src.b2","Backblaze B2","Read via S3-compatible endpoint","a"],["src.kafka","Apache Kafka","Batch-consume up to maxRecords messages from a single partition via the pure-Rust `rskafka` driver. Emits {offset, key, value, timestamp_ms} rows. startOffset negative = read from earliest available; positive = read from that offset. Batch ETL semantics - continuous streaming is on the roadmap.","a"],["src.pulsar","Apache Pulsar","","p"],["src.redpanda","Redpanda","Same wire protocol as Kafka - rides the rskafka driver. Use src.kafka semantics: batch-consume up to maxRecords from a single partition.","a"],["src.nats","NATS JetStream","Subscribe-with-timeout collector via the pure-Rust `async-nats` driver. Drains up to maxRecords messages from subject within timeoutMs wall-clock. Emits {subject, payload} rows. Batch ETL semantics - continuous streaming is on the roadmap.","a"],["src.rabbit","RabbitMQ","Pull messages from a queue via the pure-Rust `lapin` AMQP 0.9.1 driver. Polls until maxMessages or timeoutMs wall-clock elapses; auto-acks each pulled message. Emits {payload, routing_key, exchange, delivery_tag} rows.","a"],["src.kinesis","AWS Kinesis","Single-shard Kinesis read via direct HTTP + AWS SigV4 (no AWS SDK). Walks ListShards -> GetShardIterator -> GetRecords. Props: region, accessKeyId, secretAccessKey, sessionToken (optional STS), streamName, shardIndex (default 0), iteratorType (TRIM_HORIZON or LATEST), maxRecords. Records with JSON-object payloads unfold as rows; others land as {partition_key, sequence_number, data}. Multi-shard parallelism deferred.","a"],["src.eventhubs","Azure Event Hubs","","p"],["src.pubsub","GCP Pub/Sub","Pull messages via the Pub/Sub REST API (POST /v1/projects/{p}/subscriptions/{s}:pull) - sidesteps the gRPC build dependency. Auto-acks the batch. Auth via a pre-fetched OAuth2 Bearer access token (mint with `gcloud auth print-access-token`). Emits {message_id, publish_time, data} rows.","a"],["src.rest","REST","Generic HTTP GET/POST source. Parses JSON response, optionally walks a JSON pointer (responsePath) to find the row array, and follows cursor-style pagination if configured (cursorNextPath + cursorParam).","a"],["src.graphql","GraphQL","POST a GraphQL query to an endpoint and walk the response data path. Rides snk.rest/src.rest infrastructure; auth via Bearer / API-Key.","a"],["src.grpc","gRPC","","p"],["src.webhook","Webhook","Bind 127.0.0.1:port and collect up to `maxRequests` inbound HTTP requests with a global `timeoutMs` deadline. JSON-object bodies become the row; JSON-array bodies unfold into rows; other bodies fall back to {method, path, body, headers}. Local-only by design - point a tunnel (ngrok / cloudflared) at the port for public reach.","a"],["src.soap","SOAP","SOAP / generic XML-API source. Thin alias over src.rest with defaults: POST, Content-Type text/xml; charset=utf-8, responseFormat=xml. Set responsePath to the element-name walk into the body (e.g. Envelope/Body/GetUsersResponse/Users/User), supply the XML envelope in `body`, optionally add a `soapAction` prop for the SOAPAction header.","a"],["src.odata","OData","OData v4 source - thin alias over src.rest. Defaults: responsePath /value, pagination follows @odata.nextLink as a complete URL. Set authType (basic / bearer / apikey) on the form. Works with SAP, D365, Microsoft Graph, any OData v4 endpoint.","a"],["src.mongodb","MongoDB","Read documents from a MongoDB collection via the official Rust driver (find with optional filter / projection / limit). Auth via mongodb:// connection string.","a"],["src.cassandra","Cassandra","Read CQL via the scylla driver (works with both Cassandra and ScyllaDB).","a"],["src.scylla","ScyllaDB","Read CQL via the scylla driver. Same wire as src.cassandra.","a"],["src.redis","Redis","SCAN keys matching a pattern (default *) and GET each value via the sync `redis` Rust client. Emits {key, value} rows. limit caps the walk so a million-key DB doesn't spin forever.","a"],["src.dynamodb","DynamoDB","Scan a DynamoDB table via direct HTTP + AWS SigV4 signing (no aws-sdk-rust dep). Auto-unwraps the typed-attribute response shape ({S: x}, {N: 5}, {BOOL: t}, {L: [...]}, {M: {...}}) into plain JSON. Pagination follows LastEvaluatedKey. Props: region, accessKeyId, secretAccessKey, sessionToken (optional, for STS), tableName, limitPerPage (default 1000), maxPages (safety net, default 100).","a"],["src.elastic","Elasticsearch","Read docs from an Elasticsearch index via the _search API. from+size pagination (up to 10000 rows by default); ApiKey auth.","a"],["src.opensearch","OpenSearch","Read docs from an OpenSearch index via the _search API. Same wire as Elasticsearch; same ApiKey auth.","a"],["src.couchdb","CouchDB","Read CouchDB documents via the _all_docs endpoint (include_docs=true). Rides src.rest - Basic auth, responsePath /rows, cursor pagination via `next_key` if configured.","a"],["src.ftp","FTP","List + download files from an FTP server via the pure-Rust suppaftp client. Glob pattern filter (`*`, `?`); each file becomes one row {filename, size, modified, content_b64}. Use DuckDB `from_base64(content_b64)` downstream for the raw bytes. SFTP is a separate protocol and a separate component.","a"],["src.http","HTTP","Read CSV / Parquet / JSON from any HTTP(S) URL via httpfs","a"],["src.email","Email (IMAP)","Fetch the N most recent messages from an IMAP mailbox. TLS via rustls (default port 993). Basic auth (user/password). Each message becomes a row {uid, from, to, subject, date, body_text}. OAuth (gmail / o365) is on the roadmap.","a"],["src.git","Git Repository","Read commit log or file tree from a local git working copy. Shells out to the system `git` CLI - no extra Rust dep. mode=log emits {hash, short_hash, author_name, author_email, date, subject}; mode=files emits {mode, type, hash, size, path}.","a"],["src.clipboard","Clipboard","Read the system clipboard via pure-Rust arboard. If the text parses as JSON-array-of-objects each element becomes a row; otherwise a single {text, length} row is emitted. Fails clearly on headless Linux (no display server) - desktop-only by design.","a"],["src.pgvector","pgvector (Postgres)","Read embeddings + metadata via DuckDB postgres ATTACH (server must have CREATE EXTENSION vector)","a"],["src.pinecone","Pinecone","Fetch or similarity-search vectors (Pinecone has no list-all-vectors endpoint; the proper shape is a query node, on the roadmap)","v"],["src.qdrant","Qdrant","Scroll all points in a Qdrant collection via /collections/{id}/points/scroll. Cursor pagination on `result.next_page_offset`; emits {id, ...payload[, vector]} rows. apiKey via api-key header.","a"],["src.weaviate","Weaviate","List Weaviate objects via GET /v1/objects?class=&after=. Cursor pagination on the last object's id; emits {id, ...properties[, vector]} rows. apiKey via Bearer.","a"],["src.chroma","Chroma","","v"],["src.milvus","Milvus","Query Milvus via POST /v1/vector/query. Offset pagination on `offset` + `limit`; emits each `data[]` element as a row. Provide a filter expression (default `id > 0`) and optional outputFields. apiKey via Bearer.","a"],["src.lancedb","LanceDB","Read a Lance table (local dir, LanceDB Cloud db://, or s3:// / gs:// / az:// object store) via the bundled duckle-lance sidecar.","a"],["src.salesforce","Salesforce","Salesforce REST. Riders the generic src.rest path with Bearer OAuth token; users typically point url at https://{instance}.my.salesforce.com/services/data/v60.0/query/?q=SELECT+... and walk responsePath /records.","a"],["src.hubspot","HubSpot","HubSpot REST. Bearer auth via a Private App access token. Cursor pagination on `paging.next.after` (cursorNextPath /paging/next/after, cursorParam `after`). responsePath /results.","a"],["src.pipedrive","Pipedrive","Pipedrive REST. URL ?api_token=... or Bearer auth. Cursor pagination on `additional_data.pagination.next_start` (start parameter). responsePath /data.","a"],["src.zendesk","Zendesk","Zendesk Support REST. Basic auth (email/token + API token). Cursor pagination via `meta.after_cursor` + `page[after]` param. responsePath /tickets (or whatever resource).","a"],["src.intercom","Intercom","Intercom REST. Bearer auth. Cursor pagination via `pages.next.starting_after` + `starting_after` param. responsePath /data.","a"],["src.stripe","Stripe","Stripe REST. Bearer auth with the Secret Key (sk_live_... / sk_test_...). Cursor pagination on `data[-1].id` via `starting_after`. responsePath /data.","a"],["src.quickbooks","QuickBooks","QuickBooks Online REST. Bearer OAuth token; users assemble the query URL (Intuit's API requires SQL-like queries). responsePath /QueryResponse.","a"],["src.xero","Xero","Xero REST. Bearer OAuth token; pass Xero-Tenant-Id as a custom header. responsePath defaults to a top-level resource key (e.g. /Invoices/Invoices).","a"],["src.shopify","Shopify","Shopify Admin API. Bearer auth via X-Shopify-Access-Token. Link header pagination supported by recent Admin API endpoints. responsePath depends on resource (e.g. /products).","a"],["src.notion","Notion","Notion REST. Bearer integration token + Notion-Version header. Cursor pagination on `next_cursor` (cursorNextPath /next_cursor, cursorParam `start_cursor`). responsePath /results.","a"],["src.airtable","Airtable","Airtable REST. Bearer Personal Access Token. Cursor pagination on `offset` (cursorNextPath /offset, cursorParam `offset`). responsePath /records.","a"],["src.asana","Asana","Asana REST. Bearer Personal Access Token (https://app.asana.com/0/my-apps). Cursor pagination on `next_page.offset` (cursorNextPath /next_page/offset, cursorParam `offset`). responsePath /data. Base URL https://app.asana.com/api/1.0.","a"],["src.trello","Trello","Trello REST. Anonymous-style auth: append `?key={apiKey}&token={token}` to the URL. No body, no pagination (the API returns full result sets by default). Set responsePath empty since responses are top-level arrays. Base URL https://api.trello.com/1.","a"],["src.clickup","ClickUp","ClickUp REST. Bearer Personal API token (pk_... from Settings > Apps). Page pagination on `?page=N` (paginationType `page`, pageParam `page`). responsePath /tasks (or whatever resource). Base URL https://api.clickup.com/api/v2.","a"],["src.monday","Monday.com","Monday.com GraphQL. Rides src.graphql; auth via Bearer token in Authorization header. POST a GraphQL query as `body`; responsePath /data.<query_name>. Base URL https://api.monday.com/v2.","a"],["src.gsheets","Google Sheets","","p"],["src.excel-online","Microsoft Excel Online","","p"],["src.github","GitHub","GitHub REST. Bearer Personal Access Token. Link header pagination (paginationType `link`). Accept: application/vnd.github+json header recommended; defaults to https://api.github.com.","a"],["src.gitlab","GitLab","GitLab REST. Bearer Personal Access Token. Link header pagination (paginationType `link`). Base URL https://gitlab.com/api/v4 (or self-hosted).","a"],["src.linear","Linear","Linear GraphQL. Rides src.graphql; auth via API key in Authorization header. responsePath walks /data.<query>.<edges> or similar.","a"],["src.jira","Jira","Jira Cloud REST. Basic auth (email + API token). Offset pagination on `startAt` + `maxResults`. responsePath /issues for /search.","a"],["src.mailchimp","Mailchimp","Mailchimp REST. Bearer API key (the key has a region suffix - the URL is https://{region}.api.mailchimp.com/3.0). Offset pagination via `offset` + `count`. responsePath /lists (or /campaigns / etc).","a"],["src.sendgrid","SendGrid","SendGrid REST. Bearer API key. Offset pagination via `offset` + `limit`. responsePath /result for /v3/marketing/* endpoints.","a"],["src.segment","Segment","Segment Public API. Bearer access token. Cursor pagination via `pagination.next` + `pagination[cursor]` param. responsePath /data.","a"],["src.slack","Slack","Slack Web API. Bearer Bot User OAuth Token (xoxb-...). Cursor pagination via `response_metadata.next_cursor` + `cursor` param. responsePath depends on endpoint (e.g. /messages for conversations.history). Base URL https://slack.com/api.","a"],["src.discord","Discord","Discord REST. Bot token in Authorization header (prefix `Bot `). No native pagination on most endpoints; use `?limit=N&before=ID` patterns. responsePath empty (responses are top-level arrays). Base URL https://discord.com/api/v10.","a"],["src.telegram","Telegram Bot","Telegram Bot API. Token in URL path (https://api.telegram.org/bot{token}/getUpdates). Offset pagination via `?offset=N`. responsePath /result. No auth header needed - token is in the URL.","a"],["src.twilio","Twilio","Twilio REST. Basic auth (Account SID + Auth Token). Page-cursor pagination via `next_page_uri`. responsePath depends on resource (e.g. /messages, /calls). Base URL https://api.twilio.com/2010-04-01/Accounts/{AccountSid}.","a"]],"transform":[["xf.map","Map","Visual row mapper with main + lookup inputs","a"],["xf.project","Project / Select","","a"],["xf.cast","Cast / Convert Type","","a"],["xf.rename","Rename Columns","","a"],["xf.addcol","Add Column","","a"],["xf.dropcol","Drop Columns","","a"],["xf.reorder","Reorder Columns","","a"],["xf.coalesce","Coalesce / Null Fill","Fill nulls via an expression","a"],["xf.uuid","UUID","Add a fresh UUID v4 column per row - the standard surrogate row id","a"],["xf.surrogatekey","Surrogate Key","Add a warehouse dimension key derived from the business/natural key columns: hash mode (md5 of the key, stable across runs so the same business key always maps to the same surrogate) or sequence mode (1..N integer ordered by the key). Unlike UUID (random per row), this is deterministic.","a"],["xf.compare","Compare Columns","Boolean column from comparing two row columns (=, !=, <, <=, >, >=)","a"],["xf.filter","Filter Rows","WHERE-style row filter","a"],["xf.distinct","Distinct","Drop duplicate rows","a"],["xf.sample","Sample","Random row sample","a"],["xf.topn","Top N / Limit","Keep the first N rows","a"],["xf.sort","Sort","Order rows","a"],["xf.skip","Skip / Offset","Drop the first N rows","a"],["xf.rank.filter","Top N per Group","Keep the top N rows per group, ordered by a column (row_number window + filter)","a"],["xf.fill_forward","Forward Fill","Replace NULL values with the most recent non-null value within an ordered window (time-series gap fill)","a"],["xf.fill_backward","Backward Fill","Replace NULL values with the next non-null value within an ordered window (pandas-style bfill / fill up)","a"],["xf.fill_constant","Constant Fill","Replace NULL values with a literal value (numbers pass through unquoted; everything else is treated as a string)","a"],["xf.groupby","Group By","","a"],["xf.rollup","Rollup","","a"],["xf.cube","Cube","","a"],["xf.aggwin","Window Aggregate","Aggregate over a window, keep every row","a"],["xf.cumulative","Cumulative","Running sum / avg / count / min / max over an ordered window","a"],["xf.count","Count Rows","","a"],["xf.approx.quantile","Approx Quantile","Approximate quantile (median, p95, p99) via t-digest - fixed memory regardless of cardinality","a"],["xf.join.inner","Inner Join","","a"],["xf.join.left","Left Join","","a"],["xf.join.right","Right Join","","a"],["xf.join.full","Full Outer Join","","a"],["xf.join.cross","Cross Join","","a"],["xf.join.spatial","Spatial Join","Two-input join whose predicate is ST_Intersects / Contains / Within / Touches / Crosses / Overlaps / Equals","a"],["xf.lookup","Lookup","","a"],["xf.semi","Semi Join","","a"],["xf.anti","Anti Join","","a"],["xf.union","Union","Combine inputs, drop duplicates","a"],["xf.unionall","Union All","Combine inputs, keep all rows","a"],["xf.intersect","Intersect","Rows present in all inputs","a"],["xf.except","Except / Minus","Rows in the first input only","a"],["xf.rownum","Row Number","ROW_NUMBER() over a window","a"],["xf.rank","Rank","","a"],["xf.denserank","Dense Rank","","a"],["xf.lead","Lead","","a"],["xf.lag","Lag","","a"],["xf.first","First Value","","a"],["xf.last","Last Value","","a"],["xf.ntile","NTile","","a"],["xf.sessionize","Sessionize","Assign a session id to event rows by inactivity gap (clickstream / analytics prep): a new session starts when the time gap from the previous event in the partition exceeds the threshold. Emits session_id (per-partition running integer) and optionally session_seq (event index within the session).","a"],["xf.regex","Regex Replace","","a"],["xf.regex.extract","Regex Extract","Extract a capture group from a column via regexp_extract","a"],["xf.regex.match","Regex Match","Boolean: does the regex match the column? (regexp_matches)","a"],["xf.url.parse","URL Parse","Extract scheme / host / port / path / query / fragment from a URL column","a"],["xf.text.similarity","Text Similarity","Pairwise string similarity between two columns - levenshtein / damerau / jaccard / jaro-winkler","a"],["xf.text.base64","Base64","Encode a column to base64 text, or decode base64 back to bytes","a"],["xf.text.padding","Pad String","Left or right pad to a fixed length (zero-pad IDs, right-pad for fixed-width output)","a"],["xf.text.match","Text Match","Boolean: does the string contain / start with / end with a substring (DuckDB contains / starts_with / ends_with)","a"],["xf.text.reverse","Reverse","Reverse the characters of a string column","a"],["xf.text.repeat","Repeat","Repeat a string column N times","a"],["xf.text.replace","Replace (literal)","Literal substring replace (no regex metacharacters)","a"],["xf.text.slug","Slug","Generate a URL-safe slug: lowercase + hyphens, no punctuation","a"],["xf.text.strip_html","Strip HTML","Remove HTML tags from a column (regex-based, keeps the text content)","a"],["xf.split","Split","","a"],["xf.concat","Concat","","a"],["xf.trim","Trim","","a"],["xf.case","Case Change","","a"],["xf.length","Length","","a"],["xf.substring","Substring","","a"],["xf.format","Format String","","a"],["xf.hash","Hash","Hash a column (md5 / sha1 / sha256) for anonymization or deterministic IDs","a"],["xf.ip.parse","IP Parse","Extract host / family / netmask / broadcast from IP or CIDR text via the inet extension","a"],["xf.dt.parse","Parse Date","","a"],["xf.dt.format","Format Date","","a"],["xf.dt.extract","Extract Part","","a"],["xf.dt.diff","Date Diff","","a"],["xf.dt.add","Date Add","","a"],["xf.dt.trunc","Truncate","","a"],["xf.dt.tz","Timezone Convert","","a"],["xf.dt.bin","Time Bin","Round timestamps down to fixed-interval buckets (e.g. 5 minutes, 1 hour) for time-series grouping","a"],["xf.dt.now","Current Timestamp","Add a column with the pipeline run time - the standard loaded_at / processed_at stamp","a"],["xf.dt.epoch","Epoch Convert","Convert a TIMESTAMP to Unix epoch seconds, or epoch seconds back to TIMESTAMP","a"],["xf.num.round","Round","","a"],["xf.num.mod","Modulo","","a"],["xf.num.abs","Absolute","","a"],["xf.num.log","Logarithm","","a"],["xf.num.power","Power","","a"],["xf.num.sqrt","Square Root","","a"],["xf.num.bucketize","Bucketize","Bin a numeric column into N equal-width buckets between low and high (width_bucket)","a"],["xf.num.zscore","Z-Score","Per-row standardized value: (value - mean) / stddev across the whole input","a"],["xf.num.clamp","Clamp","Clip values to a [low, high] range - cap outliers before stats","a"],["xf.num.sign","Sign","Sign of a number: -1, 0, or +1","a"],["xf.pivot","Pivot","Rows to columns","a"],["xf.unpivot","Unpivot","Columns to name/value rows (wide to long)","a"],["xf.denorm","Denormalize","Collapse rows per group, joining columns into delimited cells","a"],["xf.norm","Normalize","Explode a delimited or array column into rows","a"],["xf.transpose","Transpose","Swap rows and columns","a"],["xf.json.parse","Parse JSON","","a"],["xf.json.stringify","Stringify JSON","","a"],["xf.json.flatten","Flatten","","a"],["xf.json.path","JSONPath Extract","","a"],["xf.json.merge","Merge Objects","","a"],["xf.json.array_agg","Array Aggregate","Collapse rows into a JSON array per group (json_group_array)","a"],["xf.arr.explode","Explode / Unnest","","a"],["xf.arr.collect","Collect List","","a"],["xf.arr.element","Element At","","a"],["xf.arr.contains","Contains","","a"],["xf.arr.distinct","Array Distinct","","a"],["xf.arr.length","Array Length","Scalar length of a list / array column","a"],["xf.zip","Zip Arrays to Table","Zip a headings list and a list of row-arrays (e.g. {headings:[...], rows:[[...]]}) into one row per record with a real column per heading","a"],["xf.incremental","Incremental Load","Pass only rows whose watermark column (e.g. updated_at, id) is past the last successful run. The new high-water mark is saved to workspace state and advances only when the whole run succeeds - so reruns never skip rows that were not delivered.","a"],["xf.cdc.diff","Diff Detect","Tag inserted/updated/deleted rows vs a previous snapshot","a"],["xf.diffsummary","Diff Summary","Reduce a change feed (a change_type column, e.g. from DuckLake Data Diff) to a single summary row: added / removed / updated / total_changes counts plus a ready-made summary text. Feed it into LLM Transform for an AI narrative, or into a validator to assert expected counts in CI.","a"],["xf.cdc.scd1","SCD Type 1","Resolved current state: cur + prev rows whose key is not in cur","a"],["xf.cdc.scd2","SCD Type 2","Maintain versioned history: close changed rows, insert new versions","a"],["xf.cdc.scd3","SCD Type 3","Keep the PREVIOUS value of each tracked attribute in a sibling previous_<col> column. Main input is the current rows; connect the prior snapshot to the previous (lookup) port. Per tracked column, outputs current + previous_<col> joined on the key (NULL for new keys). Optional effective-date stamp.","a"],["xf.cdc.upsert","Merge / Upsert","Emit the upsert payload: new + changed rows from cur","a"],["xf.row_hash","Row Hash (fingerprint)","Hash N columns into one fingerprint column. md5 / sha1 / sha256. Stable across runs - feed downstream diff / dedup / change detection","a"],["xf.audit","Audit Stamp","Append _loaded_at / _loaded_date / _source / _batch_id columns to every row. Standard warehouse provenance pattern","a"],["xf.ai.embed","Embeddings","Per-row embedding via any OpenAI-compatible /v1/embeddings endpoint. Props: inputColumn (default `text`), outputColumn (default `embedding`), model (default `text-embedding-3-small`), apiKey (required, sent as Bearer), baseUrl (default `https://api.openai.com` - point at Cohere, Voyage, llama.cpp embed server, etc), batchSize (default 100).","a"],["xf.ai.llm","LLM Transform","Per-row LLM completion via any OpenAI-compatible /v1/chat/completions endpoint. Props: promptTemplate with `{column}` substitution (or inputColumn for passthrough), outputColumn (default `completion`), model (default `gpt-4o-mini`), apiKey (required), baseUrl, systemPrompt, temperature. One HTTP call per row - use xf.rows.head to sample before unleashing on big tables.","a"],["xf.ai.chunk","Text Chunker","Split long text into chunks for RAG / embedding pipelines. No API call - pure local char-window splitting with overlap. Props: inputColumn (default `text`), outputColumn (default `chunk`), chunkSize (default 1000), chunkOverlap (default 100), mode (`explode` = one row per chunk with chunk_index/chunk_count, `array` = chunks as a column).","a"],["xf.ai.pii","PII Redact","Regex-based PII redaction (email, phone, SSN, credit card). No API call. Props: inputColumn (default `text`), outputColumn (defaults to input - overwrites in place), types (comma-list subset; empty = all). LLM-backed redaction is a follow-up.","a"],["xf.ai.classify","Classify","Per-row LLM-backed classification. Props: inputColumn (default `text`), outputColumn (default `category`), categories (required, comma-separated list), model (default `gpt-4o-mini`), apiKey, baseUrl. The model is prompted to pick exactly one category; anything outside the list normalizes to `UNKNOWN`. One HTTP call per row.","a"],["xf.ai.dedupe","Semantic Dedupe","Drop near-duplicate rows by cosine similarity over a pre-computed embedding column (typically from xf.ai.embed upstream). Props: embeddingColumn (default `embedding`), threshold (default 0.95). No API call; pure local math. O(N^2) - chain after xf.rows.head if your dataset is huge.","a"],["xf.ai.vector_search","Vector Similarity Search","Rank rows by similarity to a query vector via DuckDB vss","a"],["xf.ai.text_search","Full-Text Search","BM25 keyword search over text columns via DuckDB fts","a"],["xf.geo.distance","Spatial Distance","Distance from each row to a target point (ST_Distance)","a"],["xf.geo.buffer","Spatial Buffer","A buffered geometry around each row (ST_Buffer)","a"],["xf.geo.intersects","Spatial Intersects","Boolean: does each row overlap a target geometry? (ST_Intersects)","a"],["xf.log","Log Rows","Pass rows through and print them to Output","a"],["xf.assert","Assert","Hard-fail the pipeline if any row violates a SQL predicate (defensive ETL check)","a"],["xf.dbt","dbt","Run dbt against the pipeline's DuckDB database. Either write one inline model right here (reference the upstream node as {{ var('duckle_input') }}), or set `projectDir` to an existing dbt project (folder with dbt_project.yml). The engine generates the dbt-duckdb profiles.yml automatically, so models read upstream node tables and downstream nodes read the models dbt builds. Set `command` (default `run`); optional `outputModel` reads a built model back as the node output. dbt is set up automatically on first launch, so no manual install is needed.","a"]],"sink":[["snk.csv","CSV","","a"],["snk.tsv","TSV","Write tab-separated files","a"],["snk.json","JSON","","a"],["snk.jsonl","JSONL / NDJSON","","a"],["snk.xml","XML","Write rows as XML via `quick-xml`. Default shape: `<root><row><col>val</col>...</row>...</root>`. rootElement / rowElement override the wrapper names. Complex (object/array) cell values are JSON-encoded inside CDATA so the file round-trips back through src.xml losslessly.","a"],["snk.excel","Excel (XLSX)","Write .xlsx via the DuckDB excel extension","a"],["snk.parquet","Parquet","","a"],["snk.vortex","Vortex","Write rows as a Vortex columnar file (.vortex) via the bundled duckle-lance sidecar. Next-gen columnar format with fast random access; the engine bridges the upstream rows through Parquet into Vortex.","a"],["snk.avro","Avro","Write rows as an Apache Avro container file via the pure-Rust `apache-avro` crate. Schema is inferred from the first row's column types (long / double / string / boolean) - or supply a JSON Avro schema via the schemaJson field to override. recordName names the inferred record (default `Row`).","a"],["snk.qvd","Qlik QVD","Write rows as a Qlik QVD file (.qvd) via a clean-room pure-Rust encoder (no Qlik runtime). Builds the per-column symbol tables + bit-stuffed index; values are typed per cell (int / double / string), nulls preserved. Round-trips with the QVD source and loads in QlikView / Qlik Sense.","a"],["snk.orc","ORC","","p"],["snk.yaml","YAML","Write the upstream rows as a top-level YAML array (`- key: value` per row).","a"],["snk.toml","TOML","Write the upstream rows as TOML. TOML disallows a top-level array so the engine wraps under a `rows` key: `[[rows]]` per row.","a"],["snk.spatial","Geospatial (GeoJSON / GeoPackage / ...)","Write geospatial files via the spatial extension","a"],["snk.ftp","File Transfer","Upload pipeline output over FTP / FTPS / SFTP","a"],["snk.iceberg","Apache Iceberg","Write a full Iceberg table (data/ + metadata/) via DuckDB v1.5","a"],["snk.ducklake","DuckLake","Write a table into a DuckLake catalog","a"],["snk.postgres","PostgreSQL","Write to PostgreSQL via the DuckDB postgres extension","a"],["snk.cockroach","CockroachDB","Write to CockroachDB via the DuckDB postgres extension (Cockroach speaks the Postgres wire protocol)","a"],["snk.mysql","MySQL","Write to MySQL via the DuckDB mysql extension","a"],["snk.mariadb","MariaDB","Write to MariaDB via the DuckDB mysql extension (MariaDB speaks the MySQL wire protocol)","a"],["snk.sqlserver","SQL Server","INSERT to SQL Server via TDS (multi-row VALUES batched at 1000 rows, the SQL Server cap).","a"],["snk.oracle","Oracle","INSERT to Oracle via the official `oracle` Rust crate. Built into the shipped binary - users need Oracle Instant Client on the library path at runtime. Multi-row INSERT ALL ... SELECT 1 FROM dual idiom batched at 1000 rows.","a"],["snk.teradata","Teradata","Write to Teradata through its free ODBC driver. Install the Teradata ODBC driver, then connect with friendly fields, a DSN, or a full ODBC connection string. Append creates the table if missing then appends; Overwrite clears it first. No upsert.","a"],["snk.sqlite","SQLite","Write a table into a SQLite file","a"],["snk.duckdb","DuckDB","Write a table into a DuckDB file","a"],["snk.clickhouse","ClickHouse","INSERT to ClickHouse via the HTTP interface (FORMAT JSONEachRow). Batched at 10k rows by default.","a"],["snk.jdbc","Generic JDBC","","p"],["snk.motherduck","MotherDuck","Write a table into MotherDuck via ATTACH md:","a"],["snk.quack","DuckDB Quack","Write a table to a remote DuckDB instance over the Quack protocol (HTTP on port 9494). Supports append / overwrite / truncate / upsert modes via the standard relational sink path.","a"],["snk.gizmosql","GizmoSQL","Write rows to a table on a GizmoSQL (Arrow Flight SQL) server via CREATE + batched INSERT over the clean-room pure-Rust Flight SQL client. Append or overwrite; TLS optional.","a"],["snk.snowflake","Snowflake","INSERT to a Snowflake table via the SQL API (/api/v2/statements) with PAT (Personal Access Token) bearer auth. Multi-row INSERTs batched at 1000 rows by default.","a"],["snk.bigquery","BigQuery","Write tables to BigQuery via the duckdb-bigquery community extension","a"],["snk.redshift","Redshift","Write Redshift via the postgres ATTACH path (Postgres wire on port 5439); overwrite / append / truncate / upsert all supported via the existing PG sink modes","a"],["snk.databricks","Databricks SQL","INSERT to a Databricks table via the Statement Execution API with PAT Bearer auth. Multi-row INSERTs batched at 1000 rows; sync wait up to 50s.","a"],["snk.synapse","Azure Synapse","Azure Synapse rides the SQL Server TDS wire - same connection form as snk.sqlserver.","a"],["snk.s3","Amazon S3","Write via DuckDB httpfs","a"],["snk.gcs","Google Cloud Storage","Write via DuckDB httpfs","a"],["snk.azureblob","Azure Blob Storage","Write via the azure extension","a"],["snk.minio","MinIO","Write via S3-compatible endpoint","a"],["snk.r2","Cloudflare R2","Write via S3-compatible endpoint","a"],["snk.b2","Backblaze B2","Write via S3-compatible endpoint","a"],["snk.kafka","Apache Kafka","Produce one Kafka record per upstream row via the pure-Rust `rskafka` driver. Record key = optional keyColumn value; record value = JSON-stringified row. Records go to a single partition (partitionId, default 0); pipelined batching (default 500 records per produce call).","a"],["snk.redpanda","Redpanda","Same wire protocol as Kafka - rides the rskafka driver. Use snk.kafka semantics.","a"],["snk.pulsar","Apache Pulsar","","p"],["snk.nats","NATS JetStream","Publish each upstream row as one NATS message via the pure-Rust `async-nats` driver. Payload = JSON-stringified row. Optional subjectSuffixColumn appends a per-row suffix (subject.value) for routed multi-tenant publishing.","a"],["snk.rabbit","RabbitMQ","Publish each upstream row as one persistent-delivery-mode AMQP 0.9.1 message via the pure-Rust `lapin` driver. Configurable exchange + routingKey; empty exchange = default direct exchange (route to queue named by routingKey).","a"],["snk.pubsub","GCP Pub/Sub","Publish messages via the Pub/Sub REST API (POST /v1/projects/{p}/topics/{t}:publish). Each upstream row -> one base64-encoded message. Auth via OAuth2 Bearer access token. Batched at 100 messages per request (Pub/Sub max).","a"],["snk.kinesis","AWS Kinesis","","p"],["snk.rest","REST","HTTP POST one batched request containing the result as a JSON array (configurable method, headers, body shape)","a"],["snk.webhook","Webhook","HTTP POST one request per row, body = row JSON (configurable method + headers)","a"],["snk.graphql","GraphQL Mutation","POST a GraphQL mutation per upstream row. The mutation body can reference row fields via ${field} substitution.","a"],["snk.email","Email (SMTP)","Per-row SMTP send via pure-Rust `lettre` + rustls TLS. Props: host (required), port (default 587), user/password (optional - skip for relay-only servers), fromAddress (required), toColumn (default `to`), subjectColumn (default `subject`), bodyColumn (default `body`). Plain text only for v1; HTML / attachments are follow-ups.","a"],["snk.mongodb","MongoDB","Insert documents into a MongoDB collection via the official driver. Bulk insert_many batched at 1000 docs by default; replace mode drops the collection first.","a"],["snk.cassandra","Cassandra","INSERT rows into a Cassandra table via the scylla CQL driver (one INSERT per row; CQL has no multi-row VALUES).","a"],["snk.scylla","ScyllaDB","Same wire as snk.cassandra - INSERT via the scylla CQL driver.","a"],["snk.redis","Redis","SET each row's keyColumn -> valueColumn into Redis via the sync `redis` Rust client. Optional ttlSeconds adds an EXPIRE. If valueColumn is empty, the whole row is JSON-stringified as the value. Pipelined in chunks (default 1000).","a"],["snk.elastic","Elasticsearch","Bulk-index docs via the _bulk NDJSON API (configurable host, index, ApiKey auth)","a"],["snk.opensearch","OpenSearch","Bulk-index docs via the OpenSearch _bulk NDJSON API (same shape as Elasticsearch)","a"],["snk.pgvector","pgvector (Postgres)","Write embeddings to a Postgres table (server must have CREATE EXTENSION vector)","a"],["snk.pinecone","Pinecone","Upsert vectors to a Pinecone index via /vectors/upsert with Api-Key auth","a"],["snk.qdrant","Qdrant","Upsert points to a Qdrant collection via PUT /collections/{name}/points","a"],["snk.weaviate","Weaviate","Batch upsert objects to a Weaviate cluster via /v1/batch/objects with Bearer auth","a"],["snk.chroma","Chroma","","v"],["snk.milvus","Milvus","Insert rows to a Milvus collection via /v1/vector/insert","a"],["snk.lancedb","LanceDB","Write rows to a Lance table (create/overwrite or append) via the bundled duckle-lance sidecar.","a"]],"quality":[["qa.schemavalidate","Schema Validate","Reject rows where any expected column is null","a"],["qa.regex","Regex Match","Pass rows matching a pattern; rest to reject","a"],["qa.range","Range Check","Pass in-range rows; rest to reject","a"],["qa.notnull","Not-Null Check","Pass rows with no nulls; rest to reject","a"],["qa.unique","Uniqueness Check","Pass first per key; duplicates to reject","a"],["qa.outlier","Outlier Detection","Pass in-distribution rows; route statistical outliers (IQR or z-score over the chosen numeric column) to the reject port. NULLs and zero-spread data always pass.","a"],["qa.profile","Column Profile","Per-column stats: count, nulls, distinct, min/max, quartiles","a"],["qa.profile.adv","Column Profile (Advanced)","Rich single-column profile: count, null_count, null_pct, approx distinct, min/max, the fraction of values matching common patterns (email / integer / decimal / date), and the top-N most frequent values with counts. Long-form output: one row per metric (metric, value, count, pct).","a"],["qa.describe","Describe","Column names and types of the input","a"],["qa.histogram","Histogram","Value frequencies for a column","a"],["qa.standardize","Standardize","Trim, case-normalize, and collapse whitespace","a"],["qa.mask","Mask / Anonymize","Irreversibly mask a column in place for governance/compliance: deterministic salted-hash pseudonym (joinable across datasets), partial mask (show last N), null-out, or a constant. Pure in-engine, no data leaves your machine.","a"],["qa.dedupe","Fuzzy Deduplicate","Drop near-duplicate rows by string similarity","a"],["qa.match","Record Match","Find matching record pairs by similarity, with a score","a"],["qa.survivor","Survivorship (Golden Record)","Collapse duplicate records sharing a key into one golden record, picking each surviving field by rule: most-frequent value, most-recent / oldest (by a date column), or max / min. Applies to every non-key column at once.","a"],["qa.matchgroup","Match Grouping (Cluster IDs)","Turn a list of matched record pairs into one stable cluster id per record. Walks the transitive closure of the matches (a~b and b~c put a, b, c in one cluster) and assigns each id the cluster representative (the smallest reachable id). Pairs with Record Match. Output: id, cluster_id.","a"],["qa.expect","Expectations","Run a reusable suite of data-quality expectations (not-null, unique, in-set, in-range, regex, non-negative) and emit a scorecard: one row per rule with total, failed, pass_rate, and passed. The native, no-Python answer to declarative data contracts.","a"],["qa.contract","Data Contract","Enforce a data contract: the same rule suite as Expectations (not-null, unique, in-set, in-range, regex, non-negative), but as a GATE. Passes every row through unchanged when all rules hold, and fails the run with a clear error naming the violated rule(s) when any rule breaks. Drop it before a sink or scheduled load to block bad data in CI.","a"],["qa.freshness","Freshness Check (SLA Gate)","Assert the data is recent enough: computes data age = now - max(timestamp column) and checks it against a maxAge (in minutes / hours / days). Gate mode passes every row through unchanged when the freshest row is within the SLA and fails the run with a clear message when it is not. Report mode emits a one-row scorecard (max_timestamp, age, threshold, is_fresh) for dashboards or CI.","a"],["qa.sample.adv","Sample (Reproducible %)","Take a percentage sample of rows. Reservoir (even per-row probability) or Bernoulli (independent per row); set a seed to make the draw reproducible so the same rows are picked every run. All columns are preserved.","a"],["qa.refintegrity","Referential Integrity","Check a foreign key against a reference input (connect it to the lookup port): rows whose key exists in the reference pass through, orphan rows (key missing) route to the reject port. Pure semi-join / anti-join, no row fan-out on duplicate reference keys.","a"],["qa.link","Record Linkage","Fuzzy-link records across TWO inputs: the main input against a reference on the lookup port. Cross-compares the chosen key columns by string similarity (Jaro-Winkler or Levenshtein) and emits every candidate pair at or above the threshold as left_key, right_key, score. Unlike Record Match (self-join), this links two separate datasets.","a"],["qa.reconcile","Reconcile (Source vs Target)","Two-source reconciliation report for migrations and CDC QA. Main input is the source; connect the target to the lookup port. Joins on your key column(s) and emits one row per metric: source_rows, target_rows, rows_only_in_source, rows_only_in_target, keys_matched, plus per measure a source_sum / target_sum / difference.","a"],["qa.classify","Classify / PII Detect","Heuristically classify each column by semantic / PII type - pure regex + statistics, no model. Measures the fraction of values matching known shapes (email, SSN, credit card, IPv4, UUID, URL, phone, date) and tags the best match above a threshold. Emits a report (column, detected_type, match_rate, sample_count, is_pii); pair it with Mask / Anonymize.","a"],["qa.addressclean","Address Cleanse","","p"]],"control":[["ctl.replicate","Replicate / Tee","Send the same data to multiple downstream outputs","a"],["ctl.switch","Switch / Conditional Split","Route rows to case_1..N outputs by condition; first match wins","a"],["ctl.merge","Merge Streams","Concatenate multiple input streams (UNION ALL)","a"],["ctl.iterate","Iterate","Runs a referenced pipeline N times. Sub-pipeline gets ${ITER_INDEX} (0..N-1) substituted into its props before each call. Side-effect model - sub-pipeline output isn't composed into the parent (true block-scope iteration needs the DAG refactor in docs/dag-block-refactor.md).","a"],["ctl.foreach","For Each","Runs a referenced pipeline once per upstream row. ${ITER_INDEX} + ${ITER_ITEM_<FIELD>} (uppercased) substituted into the sub-pipeline props. Side-effect model.","a"],["ctl.wait","Wait / Delay","Sleep for a fixed number of milliseconds before passing rows through (smoke tests, rate-limit a downstream API)","a"],["ctl.schedule","Schedule","","p"],["ctl.throttle","Throttle","Insert an inter-stage delay derived from a rows-per-second target (best-effort for batch pipelines, hook is in place for streaming)","a"],["ctl.runpipeline","Run Pipeline","Reads + executes another pipeline file inline as a side effect, then passes the upstream view through unchanged. Useful for triggering helper pipelines (refresh dimension tables, kick off cleanup) without composing their output into the parent.","a"],["ctl.trigger","Trigger Pipeline","Alias of ctl.runpipeline; same executor branch.","a"],["ctl.runjob","Run Job","Calls a child pipeline (job) as a side effect, passing parent context variables that are substituted as ${VAR} into the child before it runs. Chain several Run Job nodes to build a Master Job that orchestrates child jobs in sequence. The child runs in its own temp DB; its output is not composed back into the parent.","a"],["ctl.parallelize","Parallelize","Runs the independent downstream branches wired to its outputs concurrently. The upstream input is snapshotted once and each branch reads that snapshot in its own isolated execution, joining when all finish (any branch failure fails the node).","a"],["ctl.checkpoint","Checkpoint","Pass rows through and also write a parquet snapshot to a path - the durable artifact a future run can read back via src.parquet","a"],["ctl.try","Try / Catch","Installs a fallback pipeline. If any downstream stage in this execution fails, the fallback runs as a side effect before the original error surfaces - useful for notifications, rollbacks, cleanup. Slice of the DAG-block refactor; true continuation-style try/catch needs the multi-week refactor (see docs/dag-block-refactor.md).","a"],["ctl.retry","Retry","Per-stage retry already lives in the Advanced tab (Retry attempts + Retry backoff) on every node - no separate component needed. A DAG-scoped retry block (wrap N stages, retry the whole group) still needs the DAG-block refactor; use ctl.try with a recovery fallback for now.","a"],["ctl.deadletter","Dead Letter Queue","Terminal sink for rejected rows - parquet or csv at a configurable path; conventionally wired to an upstream node's reject port","a"],["ctl.log","Log Message","Emit an info log line, then pass rows through unchanged. Use {rows} in the message for the upstream row count. Lines are written to the run log under the workspace logs/ folder (NDJSON) so Splunk / Dynatrace can ingest them.","a"],["ctl.warn","Warn","Emit a warning log line (does not fail the run), then pass rows through. Same {rows} templating and workspace log output as Log Message.","a"],["ctl.die","Die / Fail","Stop the pipeline with an error message. Condition controls when it fires: always, only when the input has rows (guard a reject branch), or only when the input is empty (guard missing data).","a"]],"code":[["code.sql","Inline SQL","Run a SELECT; upstream is `input`","a"],["code.sqltemplate","SQL Template","Parameterized SQL with ${context.var}","a"],["code.python","Python UDF","Per-row transform via a real Python 3 interpreter (full language + installed packages). Define a `process(row)` function that takes the row as a dict and returns the output dict (return None to drop the row); rows go in/out as JSON. Needs Python 3 on PATH or DUCKLE_PYTHON_BIN. Code in the `code` prop.","a"],["code.rust","Rust UDF","","p"],["code.javascript","JavaScript UDF","Per-row JS transform via the pure-Rust boa interpreter (sandboxed - no fetch / fs / DOM). Define a `transform(row)` function; the engine calls it per row with the row as a JS object and uses the returned object as the output row. Helpers declared at the top of the script are shared across rows within the stage. Script in the `script` prop.","a"],["code.shell","Shell Command","Run an arbitrary shell command and emit one row with {stdout, stderr, exit_code, duration_ms}. Defaults to cmd.exe on Windows, /bin/sh on Unix. Optional timeout + workingDir. Cancellation kills the child process.","a"],["code.wasm","WebAssembly UDF","Per-row WASM transform via the pure-Rust wasmi interpreter (sandboxed - no fs / net / env access). Supply the module as `wasmB64` (base64) or `path` to a .wasm file. Module must export `memory` and a function `transform(i32, i32) -> i64` packing (out_ptr << 32) | out_len. Defaults: inputColumn=text, outputColumn=result, function=transform.","a"]]};